<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-27T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-27T17:00:00-05:00" n="22" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d22">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">883.0513/180: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Fish</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-27T17:00:00-05:00">November 27, 1936—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>43. Tour 67, November 27, 1 p.m. Department is still corresponding with
                            possible candidates and hopes to submit list in near future, possibly
                            next week.</p>
                        <p>In the event Hill is not included in list of candidates, do you consider
                            that Egyptian authorities are likely to put forward his name as
                            counterproposal, as intimated by Judge Booth (see page 5, Legation’s
                            despatch 800, October 15<note n="18" xml:id="d22fn18">Not
                                printed.</note>)?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>